image.altText: Black smoke rises from a the scene of a firey car and truck collision.

props.synopsis: Multiple patients and two first responders have been injured after a cattle truck and two cars collided in a firey crash south of Brisbane.

title.children: Four motorists, baby, two first responders involved in Ipswich car accident

image.altText: Two men smiling

props.synopsis: Detectives this morning returned to the Sydney home of Jesse Baird with Commissioner Karen Webb calling for patience as police determine what happened to Mr Baird and his partner Luke Davies.

title.children: NSW Police 'working around the clock' to find answers over alleged murders of Sydney couple

image.altText: Donald Trump kisses the American flag on stage at a conference

props.synopsis: Seconds after polls closed, Donald Trump was declared victorious in Nikki Haley's home state – shattering the prospects of his only remaining rival. But she's not giving up yet.

title.children: 'You're fired, Joe': Confident Trump revives reality TV persona after big win in South Carolina

image.altText: an old photo of a woman

props.synopsis: When he was 22, Henry Petersen read the story of an unsolved 1930s era murder in his hometown. Now he wants to ensure the victim, a 19-year-old sex worker, is not forgotten.

title.children: Murdered sex worker Jean Morris's body lies in an unmarked grave in Queensland. Now locals want to change that

image.altText: A line of new houses with identically coloured black roofs.

props.synopsis: As more high-income households have shifted into the private rental market, low-income renters are struggling to complete and many are retreating into informal living arrangements, Gareth Hutchens writes.

title.children: More 'rich' households are renting, and low-income renters are struggling to compete

image.altText: A graphic showing various colourful bubbles imposed over an image of a classroom.

props.synopsis: Universities could soon be facing major funding changes as the biggest review of the sector in decades calls for a radical reshaping of the tertiary education sector.

title.children: Long-awaited report recommends sweeping changes to tertiary education

image.altText: A young couple sit smiling in a pub courtyard

props.synopsis: There are no traffic lights in this rural Queensland town and with just three stop signs and one main street, it's well off the beaten track. But to these young couples from different cities and continents, it has become home.

title.children: Why young couples are ditching the city for 'the middle of nowhere'

image.altText: Sperm injection process

props.synopsis: When a hospital patient wandered into a US fertility clinic and destroyed frozen embryos, they caused a chain of events that led to a major court ruling. It's left the IVF sector reeling, and patients in limbo.

title.children: A hospital patient dropped frozen embryos onto a clinic floor. What followed has rocked IVF in the US

image.altText: Lieutenant General Michelle McGuinness

props.synopsis: The federal government taps a 30-year veteran of the Australian military to be the next national cyber security coordinator.

title.children: Governmment taps senior military figure as new cyber security coordinator

image.altText: An emergency services ute with a boat on the roof is parked in front of a flooded road.

props.synopsis: Residents in Tully are isolated by flood waters after 400 millimetres fell on the town, and the Bureau of Meteorology is warning there may be more to come as far south as Bundaberg.

title.children: Roads cut and residents isolated after more than 300mm hammers north Queensland

image.altText: A composite photo of four celebrities

props.synopsis: The SAG awards usually offer up a blend of looks that are bold, but more elegant than the wackiness we saw on the Grammys red carpet. Here are some of the looks we've seen so far.

title.children: Screen Actors Guild red carpet: It's the era of abstract cut outs, slits, cheeky sheers and a battle of the wraps

image.altText: Billie Meryl and Pedro

props.synopsis: Oppenheimer wins best cast in a motion picture to continue its dominance this season ahead of the Oscars. Follow live.

title.children: SAG awards best moments: Fan favourites reunite, 'drunk' acceptance speech and a reignited Oscars race

image.altText: A woman stands on stage next to a large trophy.

props.synopsis: Here is the full list of winners, where there were plenty of upsets but ultimately nothing could stop the Oppenheimer juggernaut.

title.children: SAG awards winners list: Oppenheimer reigns, The Bear sweeps comedy and Succession misses lead acting nods

image.altText: Tom Gleeson on the set of Hard Quiz gesturing behind him with a serious expression.

props.synopsis: I s'pose you think you'll get these trivia questions right — for a change. Well, let's see about that.

title.children: Do you like your Sunday coffee with a side of shame? I've got the quiz for you

image.altText: Australia's T20 team huddles around the Chappell-Hadlee Trophy

props.synopsis: Australia endures three rain delays on its way to a clean sweep of its T20I series with New Zealand, posting a 27-run win in Auckland.

title.children: Australia completes T20 series sweep of New Zealand in rain-shortened game three

image.altText: Composite of a man wearing an orange mankini while on a horse

props.synopsis: Australian Sports Commission chief executive Kieran Perkins finds no humour in the sight of three-time Olympic equestrian Shane Rose appearing in a mankini, describing the incident as setting a poor example.

title.children: 'Horrified' Olympic great Kieran Perkins condemns equestrian's mankini incident

image.altText: Women protest wearing white underwear with red paint to represent blood from sexual violence.

props.synopsis: There is growing evidence rape is being used as a widespread weapon of war in the Ukraine, but it's still rare for survivors to speak out. A growing network of women are sharing their stories in the hope to seek justice for conflict-related sexual violence and uncover the extent of these hidden crimes.

title.children: 'Praying for death': Survivors uncover horrors of rape as a weapon of war in Ukraine

image.altText: Jai is wering a black shirt and pants. He is walking with his hand in the air and a big smile on his face

props.synopsis: Two years ago, 16-year-old Dhungutti boy Jai Kalani Wright died after a collision with an unmarked police car. A NSW police officer is now facing criminal charges. Jai's family is determined to seek out the truth.

title.children: Jai was celebrating his big brother's 18th birthday, the next day he was in a coma

image.altText: Laptop with community facebook page on screen, Darin's hands on keyboard

props.synopsis: Community Facebook page administrators have the same responsibilities as traditional media, but moderators may not have the background to understand everything that comes with it and also face increasing pressure to ward off scammers.

title.children: Social pages can be a vital community voice, but their toxic tendencies are a moderation risk

image.altText: Little girl being examined by a doctor.

props.synopsis: New data suggests that adults without concession cards might be finding it harder to find a GP that bulk-bills — but that's only one part of the picture.

title.children: GP bulk-billing rates are falling but there are other doctors who charge much larger out-of-pockets

image.altText: modified jet plane in grey sky

props.synopsis: A team of German scientists have spent 150 hours flying up to 15 kilometres above sea level in a modified plane packed with research instruments in an ongoing project to help refine climate modelling.

title.children: Germans measuring cloud chemistry high above Australia in flying 'HALO' laboratory

image.altText: A man looking at the camera with two people playing video games behind him.

props.synopsis: Modern gaming finds an unlikely home in the Top End, with Darwin's most storied pub in the heart of the city becoming a new esports and technology centre.

title.children: In Darwin, esports and tech take over the city's oldest pub

image.altText: Jenny Valentish, in white crop top and short red shorts, has shocked expression and arms raised, surrounded by clear water.

props.synopsis: Journalist Jenny Valentish decided to try a different wellness practice each week in order to discover which ones actually work.

title.children: Jenny Valentish turned herself into a 'human lab rat' to sift the wellness truth from fiction

image.altText: A close up of Donald Trump wearing a suit and tie.

props.synopsis: Mr Trump defeats his lone remaining challenger for the presidential nomination, former UN ambassador Nikki Haley, in her home state.

title.children: Donald Trump wins South Carolina Republican primary, defeating Nikki Haley in her home state

image.altText: A woman wearing a police hat

props.synopsis: NSW Police Commissioner Karen Webb says families have been "failed" after an inquiry investigated the suspicious deaths or unsolved murders — potentially motivated by gay hate bias.

title.children: 'I'm so sorry': Top cop apologises to families of NSW gay hate victims after damning report

image.altText: A composite of an evangelist and a woman holding a songbook.

props.synopsis: Gail's granddaughter is joining 600,000 others seeing Taylor Swift this week. Not to brag, but Gail also remembers Billy Graham's crusade 65 years ago where he spoke to an audience totalling 3 million — nearly a third of Australia's population at the time.

title.children: Think Taylor Swift can draw a crowd? The numbers pale in comparison to Billy Graham's 1959 Australian tour

image.altText: woman smiling

props.synopsis: A group of aspiring models from across Australia are forging new social connections and tapping into confidence through fashion. But there's still plenty more "exposure" needed for models living with a disability.

title.children: MS hasn't stopped Kate modelling but she still questions fashion's disability 'ethos'

image.altText: A person holds a number of dead baby turtles in their hands. Sand can be seen on the beach behind them.

props.synopsis: North and South Goulburn Island are two of Australia's most untouched nesting and foraging areas for endangered green turtles and critically endangered hawksbill turtles. But as climate change causes the sea level to rise, erosion is consuming the beach.

title.children: Climate change is consuming the beach on this remote island. It's devastating for turtle nesting

image.altText: Isla and Tegan in Leopold Cafe in 2008 before the attack

props.synopsis: Less than an hour after Isla left a Mumbai cafe, it became a terrorist target. Did her intuition save her, and should we always trust that "sixth sense"?

title.children: When is a 'bad feeling' actually bad news? Psychologists say not everything is a coincidence

image.altText: A stylised picture showing a diver mid-dive, a water polo player preparing to throw, and a Para Matildas player smiling

props.synopsis: Female athletes are more likely to use some form of hormonal contraceptives, but they don't know much about them or the menstrual cycle and it is affecting their performance and health.

title.children: 'A total disaster': The challenges athletes face when using hormonal contraceptives

image.altText: inset headshot of a white woman smiling over the exterior of a woolworths checkout

props.synopsis: Woolworths' new boss Amanda Bardwell faces an uphill battle to win back public trust when she steps into the role, experts say.

title.children: Woolworths has named its new CEO — here's why experts say it could just be 'history repeating itself'

image.altText: A colourful illustrations shows the neon paths of computer circuits arranged to resemble an illuminated human brain.

props.synopsis: The US and China have agreed to discuss a framework for automated weapons and artificial intelligence in a bilateral dialogue later this year, but experts remain sceptical.

title.children: 'Not going to stop': Concerns around AI are now forcing the US and China to cooperate — but not everyone's convinced

image.altText: An orange explosion on the horizon over a city skyline at night

props.synopsis: In a joint statement, the allies say the strikes, with Australia's support, were against 18 Houthi targets across eight locations in Yemen, including underground weapons and missile storage facilities, air defence systems, radars and a helicopter.

title.children: 'Houthis will bear the consequences': US and British forces carry out additional strikes in Yemen over Red Sea attacks

image.altText: Co-hosts Nick Kroll and John Mulaney carry Andy Samberg offstage at the 2018 Independent Spirit Awards.

props.synopsis: From Andy Samberg predicting the megastars of tomorrow to Adam Sandler's killer acceptance speech, the Independent Spirit Awards has always churned out gold.

title.children: The Independent Spirit Awards is the most entertaining ceremony you've never heard of
